President Muhammadu Buhari has joined the National Working Committee (NWC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) to mourn the death of the National Welfare Secretary of the party, Friday Nwosu. In a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, Buhari noted that the death of Nwosu has created a vacuum in the catering segment of the ruling party. “President Muhammadu Buhari shares in the pain of loss with the National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC), following the passing of the National Welfare Secretary, Friday Nwosu. “President Buhari condoles with family members, friends and associates of the lawyer, who served the party and country diligently, remarkably handling affairs of members with care, especially during the campaigns and elections.  “The President affirms that the wisdom and maturity of the late National Welfare Secretary contributed to the successes of the party over the years, and his departure has left a vacuum in the leadership segment that caters for members and staff of the APC. “President Buhari prays that Nwosu’s soul will find eternal rest, and God’s covering over his family, ” the statement reads.